OL,3,CAnti-terrorism measures considered for
OL,4,Ccity's tourist hotspots
OL,6,FCouncillor Sally Haydon, who is
OL,7,FPlymouth City Council's cabinet member
OL,8,Ffor community safety, said: "While
OL,9,Fthere's no specific threat to Plymouth
OL,10,Fat this moment, crowded places can be
OL,11,Ftargets for terrorism.
OL,13,F"We have all seen the awful events
OL,14,Fthat have happened in other around the
OL,15,Fworld, from the tragic attack on
OL,16,FLondon Bridge in 2017, and more
OL,17,Frecently the Magdeburg car attack in
OL,18,FGermany.
